data.title: Context: I.i.14.d Minutes,
data.text: Description:Minutes of the Administrative Council which took place on 28 Apr 1983 principally concerning: motion regarding fees for job applications within the public service; motion regarding private enterprise broadcasting; and meeting with Harland and Wolfe sub-committee of the Confederation of Shipbuilders and Engineering Unions. Minutes signed by Senator Michael D[aniel] Higgins, Party Chair. Also includes: agenda; organisation committee report; circular to all constituency council secretaries concerning the formation of new branches; report of the International Secretary; Party Leaders report; list of correspondence received; Labour Women report; motion and explanatory memorandum concerning private enterprise broadcasting in the name of Michael Brennan, Raidió Teilifís Éireann (RTE) Group of Unions. (22 pp)
